1
00:00:00,193 --> 00:00:01,225
(Episode 11: Love Makes People Alike)

2
00:00:01,226 --> 00:00:02,670
Is this the picnic spot?

3
00:00:03,070 --> 00:00:05,547
(Picnic time
after the merry-go-round crying fit)

4
00:00:05,560 --> 00:00:07,074
I want to take a bite of his cheek.

5
00:00:07,671 --> 00:00:09,713
So it's quintuple Chois...

6
00:00:09,738 --> 00:00:12,513
I mean, quadruple Chois
and HUENING, right?

7
00:00:13,482 --> 00:00:14,648
Do you want to join TXT?

8
00:00:15,312 --> 00:00:17,074
(Fluffy and tiny)

9
00:00:17,099 --> 00:00:18,564
- He's a good boy.
- So cute.

10
00:00:18,589 --> 00:00:19,202
(Lovesick)

11
00:00:19,457 --> 00:00:21,501
What's up, squishy cheeks?

12
00:00:22,319 --> 00:00:23,846
(Yu Jun is surrounded by his uncles.)

13
00:00:23,871 --> 00:00:25,351
The squishiness is insane.

14
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:28,015
(Whoops!)

15
00:00:28,029 --> 00:00:29,142
(What was that?)

16
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:30,101
He hit you with his cheek.

17
00:00:30,126 --> 00:00:31,222
I almost kissed your cheek.

18
00:00:31,246 --> 00:00:32,981
Could you fall over again, please?

19
00:00:33,266 --> 00:00:36,318
(He can't hear you.
He's totally entranced by something.)

20
00:00:36,603 --> 00:00:38,338
What is he staring at?

21
00:00:38,683 --> 00:00:40,703
(I'm trapped.)

22
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:42,426
(Six overwhelming eyes oozing with love)

23
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:44,945
Look at his chubby cheeks and chin.

24
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:46,820
Can I take a bite of you?

25
00:00:46,827 --> 00:00:48,394
(Nope.)

26
00:00:48,534 --> 00:00:51,051
Maybe we're paying
too much attention to him.

27
00:00:51,168 --> 00:00:52,886
Does he need some alone time?

28
00:00:53,121 --> 00:00:54,821
Is he an introvert?

29
00:00:55,405 --> 00:00:56,174
(Granting some space?)

30
00:00:56,198 --> 00:00:57,591
Where is the bubble wand?

31
00:00:57,616 --> 00:00:58,311
Exactly.

32
00:00:58,853 --> 00:01:00,039
Do you want to eat this?

33
00:01:00,059 --> 00:01:01,128
He needed a snack.

34
00:01:01,156 --> 00:01:02,295
Want some strawberries?

35
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:03,749
(Snacks are what he needs.)

36
00:01:03,774 --> 00:01:06,873
(Hurry, I want it so bad.)

37
00:01:06,912 --> 00:01:09,036
Keeping it all for yourself?
Why not share with me?

38
00:01:09,472 --> 00:01:11,005
He eats it in one bite now?

39
00:01:11,093 --> 00:01:12,840
- Does he?
- Yu Jun.

40
00:01:13,568 --> 00:01:14,975
Yogurt too.

41
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,156
(Yogurt, the second snack)

42
00:01:16,663 --> 00:01:18,412
- It's okay.
- Look at him.

43
00:01:18,589 --> 00:01:19,646
He's a picky eater.

44
00:01:19,675 --> 00:01:20,320
Exactly.

45
00:01:20,344 --> 00:01:21,948
He loves it as long
as it's not a proper meal.

46
00:01:21,973 --> 00:01:24,465
(Yu Jun has drifted away from proper meals
and only prefers snacks.)

47
00:01:24,485 --> 00:01:25,652
That's right.

48
00:01:25,677 --> 00:01:26,304
(That's good!)
Say, "Ah."

49
00:01:27,313 --> 00:01:28,545
(He loves everything except actual meals.)

50
00:01:28,602 --> 00:01:29,923
It's good, right?

51
00:01:30,758 --> 00:01:32,926
Okay, no problem, let me feed you.

52
00:01:32,951 --> 00:01:35,259
(Five mommy birds watching
the baby bird's mouth)

53
00:01:35,284 --> 00:01:35,866
Yu Jun.

54
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:38,758
(What is that?)

55
00:01:38,985 --> 00:01:40,909
(A mind-blowing angle)

56
00:01:41,762 --> 00:01:44,004
What is that? Say hello to it.

57
00:01:44,876 --> 00:01:46,172
- Are you feeling good?
- Baby.

58
00:01:47,673 --> 00:01:51,496
(A picturesque afternoon yogurt mukbang)

59
00:01:51,643 --> 00:01:53,446
Let go of the spoon.

60
00:01:54,223 --> 00:01:56,223
(A happy stomp that means it's delicious)

61
00:01:56,317 --> 00:01:58,024
Your mood is up again?

62
00:01:58,512 --> 00:01:59,486
I'm relieved.

63
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:05,148
(A messy bonk
with yogurt all over his mouth)

64
00:02:05,173 --> 00:02:05,873
(Pouting)

65
00:02:06,137 --> 00:02:08,557
(All eyes on the little one)

66
00:02:08,610 --> 00:02:09,630
Did he finish it?

67
00:02:09,664 --> 00:02:11,764
(Time for a quick wipe)

68
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:13,434
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

69
00:02:13,459 --> 00:02:15,052
(One last spoonful left)

70
00:02:15,518 --> 00:02:17,637
- Yu Jun finished it.
- It's done.

71
00:02:18,307 --> 00:02:19,973
You did a great job.

72
00:02:20,193 --> 00:02:22,103
(Camera)

73
00:02:22,130 --> 00:02:23,810
You're making the staff sad.

74
00:02:23,835 --> 00:02:25,069
The producer is crying.

75
00:02:25,094 --> 00:02:26,411
(Can I play with it?)

76
00:02:26,451 --> 00:02:27,848
That's the producer's.

77
00:02:27,873 --> 00:02:28,812
(A bite of cheese)

78
00:02:28,837 --> 00:02:30,484
It's the producer's camera.

79
00:02:30,838 --> 00:02:32,312
What will Yu Jun do?

80
00:02:32,344 --> 00:02:33,633
(Producer: Please don't throw it.)

81
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:34,321
Bonk!

82
00:02:34,605 --> 00:02:37,485
If you're going to hold it,
can you make it face you?

83
00:02:37,518 --> 00:02:38,894
No bonking with it.

84
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:40,476
Let him hold it facing himself.

85
00:02:40,501 --> 00:02:41,729
- Hold it like this.
- Show him.

86
00:02:42,226 --> 00:02:43,397
Yu Jun, bonk.

87
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:44,898
He's turning it around.

88
00:02:44,923 --> 00:02:46,868
(The uncles just want
to take a selfie of Yu Jun.)

89
00:02:47,311 --> 00:02:48,379
Turn the camera around.

90
00:02:48,802 --> 00:02:50,160
(Explosion of cuteness)

91
00:02:50,649 --> 00:02:51,488
So cute.

92
00:02:51,489 --> 00:02:53,016
- This angle is dangerous.
- Well, he is on screen.

93
00:02:53,017 --> 00:02:54,858
He looks cute on screen,
but he turns the camera right away.

94
00:02:54,858 --> 00:02:55,912
(He's playing nicely without throwing it.)

95
00:02:56,615 --> 00:02:58,501
If he goes "bonk!" with this,
I don't think we should react.

96
00:02:58,502 --> 00:03:00,080
(Yu Jun's self-cam time)

97
00:03:00,081 --> 00:03:01,615
Do you want to have
some rice crackers too?

98
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:11,124
(An ant's-eye view from the lawn)

99
00:03:13,427 --> 00:03:14,905
After putting lotion on Yu Jun...

100
00:03:14,906 --> 00:03:16,466
- Let's take a photo!
- Yes.

101
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:18,028
(Planning to take a family photo
like human wreaths)

102
00:03:18,029 --> 00:03:18,989
The thing for Yu Jun is...

103
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:20,537
- This.
- Wait, but this is...

104
00:03:20,538 --> 00:03:23,680
"Thank you, god!"
We're wearing this, right?

105
00:03:24,602 --> 00:03:26,239
(Here you are.)

106
00:03:26,304 --> 00:03:29,225
(As expected, the cart is a must!)

107
00:03:29,226 --> 00:03:30,200
(Giggling)

108
00:03:30,336 --> 00:03:32,649
Give that to me.
I'll sneak up behind him and put it on.

109
00:03:33,271 --> 00:03:35,741
(BEOMGYU's determined steps)

110
00:03:35,749 --> 00:03:38,548
(The youngest uncle is also becoming
a human wreath for his seniors, god.)

111
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:43,052
Keep going, Yu Jun. Keep going.

112
00:03:43,563 --> 00:03:47,133
(He's more cooperative than expected.)

113
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:49,592
- Let's go, Yu Jun.
- Bonk!

114
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:54,042
(Smiling broadly while watching Yu Jun)

115
00:03:54,043 --> 00:03:54,831
So cute.

116
00:03:54,838 --> 00:03:55,913
(An adorable back view)

117
00:03:55,914 --> 00:03:57,167
Gosh, he's so cute.

118
00:03:57,167 --> 00:03:59,539
(Hi, there.)

119
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:01,573
(Bye-bye!)

120
00:04:01,587 --> 00:04:03,956
(Hehe)

121
00:04:04,015 --> 00:04:06,346
(It's me again.)

122
00:04:08,265 --> 00:04:09,832
(He seems to like going through the door.)

123
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,706
Let's leave.
(Oops)

124
00:04:11,410 --> 00:04:12,820
(Let's go back.)

125
00:04:12,950 --> 00:04:14,644
He seems to like this downhill path.

126
00:04:14,857 --> 00:04:16,299
We've got him all figured out now.

127
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:21,438
(Zooming down the hill)

128
00:04:21,439 --> 00:04:23,830
(U-turn!)

129
00:04:27,357 --> 00:04:28,768
(Endless spinning with the cart)

130
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:29,882
He's unbelievably cute.

131
00:04:33,051 --> 00:04:35,444
(We need to take him over
and get a photo.)

132
00:04:35,445 --> 00:04:37,455
Bonk!

133
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:40,866
(He suddenly checks his fashion.)

134
00:04:43,106 --> 00:04:45,681
(Now's the time!)

135
00:04:45,683 --> 00:04:46,549
(Huh?)

136
00:04:46,550 --> 00:04:47,758
(Run, BEOMGYU, run!)

137
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:50,200
(Yu Jun hurriedly chases
after the drifting cart.)

138
00:04:50,201 --> 00:04:51,521
(Catch the thief!)

139
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:54,428
(A sudden chase out of nowhere)

140
00:04:54,429 --> 00:04:56,873
That's it! Keep looking straight ahead.

141
00:04:56,874 --> 00:04:57,768
(My cart!)

142
00:04:57,769 --> 00:04:59,443
(Excited uncles)

143
00:05:00,984 --> 00:05:02,017
(Screaming)

144
00:05:02,018 --> 00:05:02,886
Stop there.

145
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,280
(Returning the cart before he cries)

146
00:05:04,281 --> 00:05:04,882
Sorry.

147
00:05:04,883 --> 00:05:07,824
(If you do that again,
I'm going to lose it!)

148
00:05:08,719 --> 00:05:11,001
(Taking this chance to fix the ribbon)

149
00:05:11,001 --> 00:05:12,289
Oh my gosh, what is that?

150
00:05:14,138 --> 00:05:16,379
- He's not bothered.
- Okay, let's go.

151
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:17,694
It's done, we did it!

152
00:05:17,929 --> 00:05:19,269
Quick, take a photo of him!

153
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:20,550
(A chance for a solo front shot!)

154
00:05:20,551 --> 00:05:22,556
(He bends over and walks backward.)

155
00:05:23,635 --> 00:05:25,221
So cute!

156
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,731
- Hey, BEOMGYU.
- Yeah?

157
00:05:27,732 --> 00:05:28,638
(BEOMGYU looks exhausted already.)

158
00:05:28,639 --> 00:05:31,347
Come over here.
Let's take a family photo.

159
00:05:31,348 --> 00:05:33,410
Yu Jun, let's go. Let's go this way.

160
00:05:33,731 --> 00:05:35,404
Coax Yu Jun nicely and bring him over.

161
00:05:37,651 --> 00:05:38,738
(Let go!)

162
00:05:38,826 --> 00:05:41,140
Yu Jun is trying to have
a power struggle with me.

163
00:05:41,549 --> 00:05:43,129
- You can beat him.
- Take him down!

164
00:05:43,703 --> 00:05:45,245
(You can feel the helplessness emanating
from him.)

165
00:05:46,059 --> 00:05:47,587
(Get your hands off it!)

166
00:05:48,529 --> 00:05:49,576
Sorry guys, I lost.

167
00:05:49,983 --> 00:05:52,839
(But BEOMGYU tries again,
grabbing the cart.)

168
00:05:52,855 --> 00:05:55,295
Sorry! Guys, I really lost.
I can't beat him.

169
00:05:55,924 --> 00:05:58,545
(Yu Jun goes off with the cart.)

170
00:05:58,746 --> 00:06:00,186
(Time for me to step in)

171
00:06:00,554 --> 00:06:01,534
He made a U-turn.

172
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:03,023
(Completely absorbed in pushing the cart)

173
00:06:05,232 --> 00:06:06,419
- Let's go this way!
- Yu Jun!

174
00:06:06,847 --> 00:06:08,666
He's really loving the little hill.

175
00:06:09,884 --> 00:06:11,451
(Sending out radio frequency)

176
00:06:12,525 --> 00:06:14,527
- Let's go!
- He doesn't like that at all.

177
00:06:16,117 --> 00:06:18,745
(After soothing him
with the airplane game)

178
00:06:18,826 --> 00:06:20,000
Here, you hold him.

179
00:06:20,409 --> 00:06:22,309
Let's wipe his mouth first.

180
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:23,230
Wait.

181
00:06:23,283 --> 00:06:27,767
(Bringing up the vibe
with Yu Jun's favorite song)

182
00:06:27,874 --> 00:06:30,143
(Singing vigorously)

183
00:06:30,632 --> 00:06:32,112
Do the "I love you" pose!

184
00:06:32,314 --> 00:06:34,594
He's doing it! Take the picture, quick!

185
00:06:36,243 --> 00:06:38,738
- Yu Jun, I love you!
- I love you!

186
00:06:39,012 --> 00:06:41,748
- One more time.
- Yu Jun, wink!

187
00:06:42,102 --> 00:06:43,543
(Winking)

188
00:06:45,445 --> 00:06:46,519
- He's done resting.
- I guess so.

189
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,768
- Well, we got the photo.
- Success!

190
00:06:48,970 --> 00:06:50,784
Yu Jun, let's send a video message
to Mommy.

191
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,440
Start with a greeting. Say hello.

192
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:54,140
Say hi to Mommy.

193
00:06:54,728 --> 00:06:55,755
"I love you, Mommy!"

194
00:06:55,804 --> 00:06:56,724
(He stands up.)

195
00:06:56,752 --> 00:06:58,879
- I love you!
- Say I love you to Mom and Dad.

196
00:06:58,993 --> 00:07:00,681
(He coolly runs away...)

197
00:07:00,734 --> 00:07:02,962
(at a speed the camera can't
keep up with.)

198
00:07:03,557 --> 00:07:04,604
Where do you think you're going?

199
00:07:04,652 --> 00:07:05,839
It's airplane time!

200
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,661
(Recharging him with more airplane time)

201
00:07:08,715 --> 00:07:10,396
Shall we leave a video message for Mommy?

202
00:07:11,287 --> 00:07:14,046
"Mommy, Daddy, thanks for raising me."

203
00:07:14,661 --> 00:07:15,854
- "I love you!"
- Now, bow.

204
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:17,897
- I love you!
- I love you!

205
00:07:18,005 --> 00:07:19,739
(Something is missing...)

206
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:21,067
- "Mommy, Daddy."
- Say, "Thank you."

207
00:07:21,275 --> 00:07:22,155
Airplane time!

208
00:07:22,935 --> 00:07:26,399
(For one last endorphin rush,
the airplane takes off.)

209
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,977
(This is so fun!)

210
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:31,951
- Let's line up!
- Get in formation.

211
00:07:31,987 --> 00:07:33,227
(He's smiling, so gather around!)

212
00:07:33,301 --> 00:07:34,394
Make sure we can see this too.

213
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,863
One more time.

214
00:07:36,931 --> 00:07:38,058
In 1, 2, 3!

215
00:07:38,252 --> 00:07:40,913
(Quickly putting him
on the airplane again)

216
00:07:41,054 --> 00:07:42,588
Where should we look?

217
00:07:42,722 --> 00:07:43,822
In 1, 2, 3!

218
00:07:43,865 --> 00:07:46,760
(Taking the photo before Yu Jun's
smiling expression disappears)

219
00:07:47,736 --> 00:07:49,769
- I love you!
- I love you!

220
00:07:49,839 --> 00:07:51,779
(Getting one photo is so difficult.)

221
00:07:51,832 --> 00:07:52,579
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

222
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:56,216
(A successful, harmonious family photo
after some ups and downs)

223
00:08:01,254 --> 00:08:03,154
Yu Jun, what kind of haircut do you want?

224
00:08:04,721 --> 00:08:07,121
I wonder how he'll look with short bangs.

225
00:08:07,121 --> 00:08:08,362
Like choppy bangs?

226
00:08:09,387 --> 00:08:10,687
He might look cute with them.

227
00:08:10,687 --> 00:08:12,054
He'll look good in anything.

228
00:08:12,054 --> 00:08:13,754
(With Yu Jun, everything is fine.)

229
00:08:13,954 --> 00:08:17,154
But will he even sit still for a haircut?

230
00:08:17,154 --> 00:08:19,521
- No way.
- Babies absolutely hate it.

231
00:08:19,521 --> 00:08:20,521
Most of them cry.

232
00:08:20,521 --> 00:08:24,454
I only remember babies
crying at the salon.

233
00:08:24,454 --> 00:08:26,021
I used to hate haircuts too.

234
00:08:26,021 --> 00:08:27,421
Same. I hated it so much.

235
00:08:28,587 --> 00:08:31,021
But he has a few random strands
sticking out on the sides,

236
00:08:31,021 --> 00:08:33,687
- so we should tidy those up.
- We just need a quick trim.

237
00:08:33,687 --> 00:08:34,854
Just neaten up the sides.

238
00:08:34,854 --> 00:08:36,621
Or we could just give him a two-block cut.

239
00:08:36,621 --> 00:08:37,621
(Pretending not to hear)
A two-block cut?

240
00:08:39,821 --> 00:08:41,654
Or should we just shave it all off?

241
00:08:42,154 --> 00:08:43,954
- Yeah, then...
- That would be refreshing.

242
00:08:43,954 --> 00:08:45,854
we won't have to bring him
back anytime soon.

243
00:08:45,854 --> 00:08:47,721
Yu Jun will look like...

244
00:08:47,721 --> 00:08:49,654
- a newborn.
- A newborn all over again.

245
00:08:51,121 --> 00:08:52,321
He's 100 percent going to cry.

246
00:08:52,321 --> 00:08:54,354
It's fine. We can just
power through the tears.

247
00:08:54,354 --> 00:08:55,387
Let him cry it out.

248
00:08:55,387 --> 00:08:57,054
- Okay.
- It happens.

249
00:08:57,654 --> 00:09:00,621
Yu Jun crossed his legs just like me.

250
00:09:01,287 --> 00:09:02,554
This isn't good.

251
00:09:02,554 --> 00:09:04,054
Looking cool, Yu Jun.

252
00:09:04,954 --> 00:09:06,921
- He can cross his legs?
- Nice.

253
00:09:06,921 --> 00:09:08,387
- Who?
- Yu Jun.

254
00:09:08,387 --> 00:09:10,587
He's growing up so fast.

255
00:09:10,587 --> 00:09:11,587
I know.

256
00:09:12,221 --> 00:09:14,021
That's the tricky part with Yu Jun.

257
00:09:14,021 --> 00:09:16,121
When we show him we're having fun,

258
00:09:16,121 --> 00:09:18,987
most babies want to join in.

259
00:09:18,987 --> 00:09:21,854
But if Yu Jun isn't interested,
he never will be.

260
00:09:21,854 --> 00:09:22,854
True.
He has his standards.

261
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:24,887
(A baby with a mind of his own)

262
00:09:29,254 --> 00:09:31,121
(Lost in thought)

263
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:34,721
(Yu Jun, a headstrong 16-month-old,
is officially bored.)

264
00:09:35,787 --> 00:09:37,687
(Spaced out)

265
00:09:38,021 --> 00:09:41,987
(Staring at something)

266
00:09:43,187 --> 00:09:45,854
(Is there something over there?)

267
00:09:46,687 --> 00:09:48,921
(What are you looking at, Yu Jun?)

268
00:09:53,354 --> 00:09:54,554
(Over there)

269
00:09:54,554 --> 00:09:55,554
Huh?

270
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:57,487
(I'm bored.)

271
00:09:57,487 --> 00:09:59,887
(Trying to read his mind)

272
00:09:59,887 --> 00:10:02,454
(Communication breakdown)

273
00:10:02,454 --> 00:10:04,221
(Glancing)

274
00:10:04,221 --> 00:10:05,721
(I said, I'm bored.)

275
00:10:05,721 --> 00:10:08,521
(Trying to send a signal again)

276
00:10:08,754 --> 00:10:11,954
(Does he want to make eye contact?)

277
00:10:13,687 --> 00:10:17,187
(I love you too, Yu Jun.)

278
00:10:17,554 --> 00:10:19,887
(Giving up)

279
00:10:20,854 --> 00:10:22,654
Yu Jun, we're here.

280
00:10:22,654 --> 00:10:24,398
I wonder if he'll handle the haircut okay.

281
00:10:24,854 --> 00:10:27,921
- I doubt it.
- I'm so nervous!

282
00:10:27,921 --> 00:10:29,021
(Will he make it through?)

283
00:10:29,521 --> 00:10:30,854
(The uncles start getting nervous.)

284
00:10:30,854 --> 00:10:34,521
- Hello.
- Hello.

285
00:10:34,521 --> 00:10:36,521
We're here for a baby haircut.

286
00:10:36,521 --> 00:10:38,121
(Where am I?)

287
00:10:38,146 --> 00:10:39,826
Just a little trimming, please.

288
00:10:39,954 --> 00:10:43,954
(First time at a hair salon with Yu Jun)

289
00:10:45,154 --> 00:10:49,487
(Featuring a special salon chair
just for babies)

290
00:10:49,787 --> 00:10:51,921
- This is so cool!
- Awesome!

291
00:10:51,921 --> 00:10:53,254
What a cute chair.

292
00:10:53,254 --> 00:10:55,087
(Will Yu Jun like it?)

293
00:10:55,087 --> 00:10:56,830
You're going to look so handsome
after this.

294
00:10:57,487 --> 00:10:59,487
- So cool.
- We haven't even put him down yet.

295
00:11:00,329 --> 00:11:03,429
(He realizes he's getting a haircut.)

296
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:04,454
It's okay.

297
00:11:04,454 --> 00:11:06,321
Look at this fancy chair.

298
00:11:06,321 --> 00:11:08,254
- Let's sit here first, okay?
- It's neat.

299
00:11:09,354 --> 00:11:10,554
Let's try putting him down.

300
00:11:10,554 --> 00:11:12,854
(I am not getting a haircut.)

301
00:11:13,121 --> 00:11:14,154
(Watching closely)

302
00:11:14,154 --> 00:11:15,687
- No?
- It's okay.

303
00:11:15,687 --> 00:11:17,854
(Save me)

304
00:11:18,654 --> 00:11:20,821
(Yu Jun loses his temper
for the first time in a while.)

305
00:11:20,821 --> 00:11:21,854
Are you crying?

306
00:11:22,687 --> 00:11:24,787
(Bursting into tears)

307
00:11:24,954 --> 00:11:26,087
Oh, dear.

308
00:11:26,787 --> 00:11:28,621
Would you like to hold him on your lap
while I cut his hair?

309
00:11:29,087 --> 00:11:30,121
We can do that?

310
00:11:30,121 --> 00:11:32,854
Yes, it'll probably be easier
if you hold him.

311
00:11:33,221 --> 00:11:34,954
- You don't like it?
- Should I hold him?

312
00:11:35,321 --> 00:11:36,321
(An expert's tip)

313
00:11:36,321 --> 00:11:38,187
We should hold him first before starting.

314
00:11:38,187 --> 00:11:40,054
What should I do? Do I wear this?

315
00:11:40,054 --> 00:11:41,721
(YEONJUN becomes the chair.)

316
00:11:41,887 --> 00:11:44,254
- You should lift him up.
- Okay.

317
00:11:44,254 --> 00:11:45,921
- Whether he cries or not.
- Sorry, Yu Jun.

318
00:11:45,921 --> 00:11:46,954
(Huh?)

319
00:11:47,254 --> 00:11:48,254
(Crying again)

320
00:11:48,254 --> 00:11:49,754
You like it? Me too.

321
00:11:51,221 --> 00:11:53,454
(Turning right back around)

322
00:11:53,454 --> 00:11:54,487
There you go.

323
00:11:55,121 --> 00:11:57,121
- Right this way, please.
- Okay.

324
00:11:57,854 --> 00:11:59,121
Let's show him first.

325
00:11:59,121 --> 00:12:00,287
(Second attempt at Yu Jun's haircut)

326
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:04,487
(Yu Jun bursts into tears
the moment he gets near the chair.)

327
00:12:04,487 --> 00:12:05,954
Are you sad?

328
00:12:05,954 --> 00:12:08,487
It's fine. We knew this would happen.

329
00:12:08,821 --> 00:12:11,654
(They expected it, but have no plan.)

330
00:12:11,654 --> 00:12:12,987
We haven't even started yet.

331
00:12:13,287 --> 00:12:14,287
Oh boy.

332
00:12:14,287 --> 00:12:17,221
(This is tough.)

333
00:12:17,221 --> 00:12:18,987
Don't cry, buddy.

334
00:12:18,987 --> 00:12:20,821
(Just crying)

335
00:12:21,587 --> 00:12:23,387
How would you like his hair cut?

336
00:12:23,387 --> 00:12:26,221
Just the messy strands
sticking out on the sides.

337
00:12:26,221 --> 00:12:27,754
We just want a quick trim.

338
00:12:27,754 --> 00:12:30,554
(Please make it quick.)

339
00:12:30,554 --> 00:12:31,754
You'll look much better after this.

340
00:12:31,754 --> 00:12:32,854
What's wrong, Yu Jun?

341
00:12:32,854 --> 00:12:35,187
(Adorable even in the midst of a meltdown)

342
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:37,364
She's going to make you look handsome.

343
00:12:37,787 --> 00:12:39,254
(I don't care.)

344
00:12:39,254 --> 00:12:40,554
Aw, you're so upset.

345
00:12:41,021 --> 00:12:42,054
All done, Yu Jun.

346
00:12:44,721 --> 00:12:45,987
It's almost over.

347
00:12:45,987 --> 00:12:46,987
(It's not.)

348
00:12:47,554 --> 00:12:53,987
(The uncles are draining fast.)

349
00:12:54,454 --> 00:12:58,154
(Yu Jun breaks down in tears.)

350
00:12:58,154 --> 00:12:59,154
Should I give him some cheese?

351
00:12:59,254 --> 00:13:01,454
Hair might get in his mouth.

352
00:13:01,454 --> 00:13:03,587
We should give him a whole piece
instead of tearing it up.

353
00:13:04,221 --> 00:13:05,421
Yu Jun!

354
00:13:05,421 --> 00:13:06,554
Almost done, Yu Jun.

355
00:13:06,554 --> 00:13:07,987
(Cheese on standby)

356
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:08,987
(Cheese?)

357
00:13:08,987 --> 00:13:10,621
Okay, show him this for a second.

358
00:13:10,621 --> 00:13:12,654
(The crying stops instantly,
thanks to his favorite cheese.)

359
00:13:12,654 --> 00:13:13,654
He's still chewing.

360
00:13:14,987 --> 00:13:15,987
More?

361
00:13:17,321 --> 00:13:20,254
(Meanwhile, the stylist's hands are busy.)

362
00:13:20,254 --> 00:13:24,387
(Snipping away despite the chaos)

363
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:25,954
Do you like the cheese?

364
00:13:25,954 --> 00:13:27,287
She's cutting a moving target.

365
00:13:28,154 --> 00:13:29,654
- She's a total pro.
- Seriously.

366
00:13:29,654 --> 00:13:31,421
It's okay.

367
00:13:31,421 --> 00:13:32,987
(Getting into the groove)

368
00:13:33,287 --> 00:13:34,554
Such a handsome boy, Yu Jun.

369
00:13:35,587 --> 00:13:37,621
You're all done. For real this time.

370
00:13:37,621 --> 00:13:39,254
Doesn't it feel nice and light now?

371
00:13:39,254 --> 00:13:40,287
It's refreshing.

372
00:13:40,287 --> 00:13:42,221
The back looks so much cleaner.

373
00:13:42,221 --> 00:13:43,254
Exactly.

374
00:13:43,987 --> 00:13:46,954
She did a wonderful job.

375
00:13:47,221 --> 00:13:48,954
Yu Jun, all done.

376
00:13:49,287 --> 00:13:50,654
- Yu Jun, it's over.
- Finished!

377
00:13:50,654 --> 00:13:52,287
- Done!
- Good boy.

378
00:13:52,287 --> 00:13:53,607
- Good job!
- It's done.

379
00:13:54,087 --> 00:13:55,787
You did so well!

380
00:13:56,487 --> 00:13:58,321
(Brushing off the loose hair)

381
00:13:58,321 --> 00:13:59,954
You did amazing!

382
00:13:59,954 --> 00:14:02,521
(Showering him with compliments
to keep the tears at bay)

383
00:14:02,821 --> 00:14:04,787
- Great job, buddy!
- Great job!

384
00:14:05,087 --> 00:14:06,187
(That was exhausting.)

385
00:14:06,187 --> 00:14:07,421
Don't give him a chance to cry.

386
00:14:09,521 --> 00:14:11,654
(Making airplane sounds)

387
00:14:12,007 --> 00:14:14,273
(Finishing on a high note
with one last piece of cheese)

388
00:14:14,721 --> 00:14:16,354
I'm a pro at feeding you now.

389
00:14:16,921 --> 00:14:19,054
(Feeling proud)

390
00:14:19,254 --> 00:14:21,787
(Finally out of the chair)

391
00:14:22,854 --> 00:14:23,887
Can you do my hair next, please?

392
00:14:23,887 --> 00:14:25,221
(Exhausted)

393
00:14:25,221 --> 00:14:26,487
YEONJUN's turn now.

394
00:14:27,554 --> 00:14:29,621
- Yu Jun, ready for a shampoo?
- Shampoo?

395
00:14:29,621 --> 00:14:31,354
(Time for a shampoo)

396
00:14:31,354 --> 00:14:33,121
(Crying)

397
00:14:33,387 --> 00:14:34,921
(You said we were done.)

398
00:14:34,921 --> 00:14:36,554
He's hitting high notes now.

399
00:14:37,321 --> 00:14:39,787
(Did he stop?)

400
00:14:40,554 --> 00:14:44,021
(Crying again the moment he turns around)

401
00:14:44,021 --> 00:14:46,354
- Amazing!
- Incredible!

402
00:14:46,354 --> 00:14:47,587
(Preparing for the wash)

403
00:14:47,587 --> 00:14:49,087
(He needs to lean back for the shampoo.)

404
00:14:49,087 --> 00:14:51,454
- It doesn't look that hard.
- Just lean back together like this.

405
00:14:51,454 --> 00:14:52,766
- Do we lean back together?
- Yes.

406
00:14:53,321 --> 00:14:54,621
Oh man!

407
00:14:54,621 --> 00:14:56,387
(Lying him down while holding him close)

408
00:14:56,387 --> 00:14:57,762
Incredible, amazing!

409
00:14:59,321 --> 00:15:01,087
It's okay!

410
00:15:01,087 --> 00:15:02,272
(Using BEOMGYU as a human chair)

411
00:15:02,587 --> 00:15:05,254
(Watching Yu Jun from afar)

412
00:15:05,387 --> 00:15:08,421
(I thought we were finished.)

413
00:15:08,421 --> 00:15:09,454
- Look at his bangs!
- So cute!

414
00:15:09,454 --> 00:15:11,721
Yu Jun looks so handsome from this angle.

415
00:15:11,721 --> 00:15:14,221
- Yu Jun.
- Even his forehead is perfectly round.

416
00:15:14,221 --> 00:15:16,487
- So cute.
- You're so good-looking, Yu Jun!

417
00:15:16,487 --> 00:15:17,521
(BEOMGYU can only stare at the floor.)

418
00:15:17,654 --> 00:15:18,987
He has thick eyebrows too.

419
00:15:18,987 --> 00:15:20,254
It's okay.

420
00:15:20,254 --> 00:15:21,721
I'll massage your legs for you.

421
00:15:23,521 --> 00:15:26,987
(Meanwhile, the stylist rinses
at double speed.)

422
00:15:28,521 --> 00:15:30,154
There. All done.

423
00:15:30,154 --> 00:15:31,154
Good boy.

424
00:15:31,154 --> 00:15:34,421
(A teary-eyed dumpling with rosy cheeks)

425
00:15:34,854 --> 00:15:38,121
(The grand finale: blow-drying)

426
00:15:41,021 --> 00:15:42,087
Wow.

427
00:15:42,454 --> 00:15:44,454
He cried so much. Look at his eyes.

428
00:15:44,454 --> 00:15:45,454
(Taking a bite)

429
00:15:45,454 --> 00:15:46,821
- He has no tears left.
- Totally out of tears.

430
00:15:46,821 --> 00:15:47,821
He's dehydrated.

431
00:15:48,187 --> 00:15:50,121
(The cheese supplier)

432
00:15:50,721 --> 00:15:52,121
(Three slices of cheese per salon visit)

433
00:15:52,121 --> 00:15:53,154
Is it good?

434
00:15:55,687 --> 00:15:57,754
Yu Jun, want some water? You cried a lot.

435
00:15:58,087 --> 00:15:59,921
(Rehydrating after a good cry)

436
00:15:59,921 --> 00:16:00,954
Good boy, hold it tight.

437
00:16:03,721 --> 00:16:06,421
(Keeping the cheese coming to comfort him)

438
00:16:06,421 --> 00:16:07,621
Yummy?

439
00:16:07,854 --> 00:16:10,187
(The tears have stopped,
but the runny nose begins.)

440
00:16:10,187 --> 00:16:11,654
All clean and fresh now.

441
00:16:13,354 --> 00:16:15,621
Aw, look at your runny nose.

442
00:16:16,954 --> 00:16:21,954
(Now that he's calm,
he finally notices his shampoo buddy.)

443
00:16:22,521 --> 00:16:24,421
(Still carefully brushing off loose hair)

444
00:16:24,421 --> 00:16:25,554
Cute.

445
00:16:26,021 --> 00:16:27,221
So adorable!

446
00:16:28,054 --> 00:16:30,021
(Chubby cheeks)

447
00:16:33,521 --> 00:16:34,554
Tastes good?

448
00:16:34,554 --> 00:16:36,521
(Adoring look returns.)

449
00:16:36,754 --> 00:16:37,754
High five if it's delicious!

450
00:16:38,821 --> 00:16:40,321
- Yay!
- You like it!

451
00:16:40,321 --> 00:16:41,521
Give him one more.

452
00:16:42,287 --> 00:16:44,554
(A high five gets a reward.)

453
00:16:44,554 --> 00:16:45,621
Delicious!

454
00:16:46,054 --> 00:16:48,787
(The GGUM Cleaning Service
is back in action.)

455
00:16:49,554 --> 00:16:52,487
(The human lint rollers)

456
00:16:52,787 --> 00:16:55,154
Your feet might tickle later, Yu Jun.

457
00:16:55,687 --> 00:16:58,954
(Carefully removing
every single stray hair)

458
00:16:59,754 --> 00:17:00,754
Mozzarella cheese!

459
00:17:00,754 --> 00:17:02,321
(Thanks to the uncles, the blowout
finishes without a single tear.)

460
00:17:02,554 --> 00:17:03,721
Yu Jun, want some styling product?

461
00:17:03,721 --> 00:17:06,054
(Custom styling session for Yu Jun)

462
00:17:06,754 --> 00:17:08,321
A little extra touch for his hair.
So cute.

463
00:17:08,521 --> 00:17:09,721
Your hair looks so nice.

464
00:17:10,087 --> 00:17:14,087
(The look is complete
after only two crying fits.)

465
00:17:14,387 --> 00:17:15,987
(A dramatic before-and-after
transformation)

466
00:17:15,987 --> 00:17:17,687
Now that his hair is styled...

467
00:17:18,087 --> 00:17:19,721
- He looks so much better.
- Yeah.

468
00:17:20,021 --> 00:17:21,021
Yu Jun, check yourself out.

469
00:17:21,687 --> 00:17:24,421
- It looks nice, right?
- Look at yourself in the mirror.

470
00:17:25,621 --> 00:17:27,087
If he goes to preschool like this...

471
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:28,187
He looks so tiny.

472
00:17:28,487 --> 00:17:30,654
- He'll get so many kisses.
- You're already young,

473
00:17:30,654 --> 00:17:31,892
but you look even younger now.

474
00:17:32,354 --> 00:17:34,121
Should I get my hair styled here too?

475
00:17:34,121 --> 00:17:36,521
Yu Jun can't possibly look
any younger, right?

476
00:17:36,521 --> 00:17:37,854
He's already peak cuteness.

477
00:17:37,854 --> 00:17:38,854
(The uncles get
competitive over his looks)

478
00:17:38,854 --> 00:17:41,421
- We're all finished!
- All done!

479
00:17:41,421 --> 00:17:42,887
- Yu Jun, you look beautiful!
- Good job today.

480
00:17:42,887 --> 00:17:44,121
- All finished.
- Why do you look so good?

481
00:17:44,121 --> 00:17:46,587
- Yu Jun, do an ending fairy pose!
- So handsome.

482
00:17:46,587 --> 00:17:47,821
Perfect!

483
00:17:47,821 --> 00:17:49,454
The ending fairy!

484
00:17:49,454 --> 00:17:51,554
Wow, he even did the pose?

485
00:17:51,554 --> 00:17:53,254
He actually did an ending pose!

486
00:17:53,754 --> 00:17:55,221
- How are you this cute?
- Good job.

487
00:17:55,954 --> 00:17:58,387
(The official visual of the group today)

488
00:17:58,387 --> 00:17:59,987
I love you, Yu Jun!

489
00:17:59,987 --> 00:18:00,987
He's smiling.

490
00:18:01,722 --> 00:18:04,156
Say, "I love you."

491
00:18:04,991 --> 00:18:05,824
"I love you."

492
00:18:06,093 --> 00:18:09,063
Yu Jun's eyes kind of look like YEONJUN's.

493
00:18:09,064 --> 00:18:10,063
What do you mean?

494
00:18:10,064 --> 00:18:13,265
- His eyes look a bit sharper now.
- Really?

495
00:18:13,266 --> 00:18:14,334
They used to be so round and soft.

496
00:18:14,335 --> 00:18:16,035
People start looking alike
when they love each other!

497
00:18:16,036 --> 00:18:17,903
He used to look so pure and innocent,

498
00:18:17,904 --> 00:18:18,670
What about now?

499
00:18:18,671 --> 00:18:20,105
but now, there's a bit more intensity
in his eyes.

500
00:18:20,106 --> 00:18:21,373
Right, they definitely got sharper.

501
00:18:22,008 --> 00:18:23,041
Let's go, Mozzarella Stick.

502
00:18:23,643 --> 00:18:24,676
Let's go.

503
00:18:25,212 --> 00:18:26,379
(Yu Jun is paying for it himself.)

504
00:18:26,513 --> 00:18:27,480
Yu Jun, go hand it over.

505
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:29,014
Say, "Please charge this."

506
00:18:29,683 --> 00:18:31,651
- And then say, "Thank you."
- Say, "Thank you."

507
00:18:32,231 --> 00:18:33,085
(Dropping it)

508
00:18:33,086 --> 00:18:34,720
- "Thank you."
- You can't just drop it like that.

509
00:18:34,721 --> 00:18:35,954
Hand it over properly.

510
00:18:36,089 --> 00:18:36,855
Okay?

511
00:18:37,457 --> 00:18:38,290
Got it?

512
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:41,293
(Using "manners education"
as an excuse to treat himself)

513
00:18:41,895 --> 00:18:43,162
- All right.
- Thank you.

514
00:18:43,163 --> 00:18:44,697
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

515
00:18:44,698 --> 00:18:45,731
(Hair salon mission accomplished)

516
00:18:45,866 --> 00:18:46,666
Let's go.

517
00:18:47,401 --> 00:18:48,301
Where should we go now?

518
00:18:49,102 --> 00:18:50,502
Let's go to the jjimjilbang.

519
00:18:50,503 --> 00:18:53,072
Let's go there and fill our stomachs.

520
00:18:53,073 --> 00:18:55,274
- Yu Jun, only fun things are left now.
- I want to eat ramyeon there.

521
00:18:55,275 --> 00:18:58,110
There's probably a ball pit there too.

522
00:18:58,111 --> 00:18:59,011
Really?

523
00:18:59,212 --> 00:19:00,145
He's going to love it.

524
00:19:01,014 --> 00:19:01,814
High five.

525
00:19:02,482 --> 00:19:03,749
- Bonk.
- Bonk!

526
00:19:04,551 --> 00:19:06,619
(I love the "Bonk" game.)

527
00:19:09,322 --> 00:19:10,623
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

528
00:19:10,624 --> 00:19:11,790
Bonk!

529
00:19:12,759 --> 00:19:13,959
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

530
00:19:14,261 --> 00:19:15,027
(This is fun.)
Bonk!

531
00:19:17,864 --> 00:19:18,730
Bonk!

532
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:20,733
Bonk!

533
00:19:21,935 --> 00:19:23,969
(This is a must-film moment.)

534
00:19:23,970 --> 00:19:25,070
Yu Jun, bonk!

535
00:19:26,206 --> 00:19:27,473
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

536
00:19:28,508 --> 00:19:29,308
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

537
00:19:30,944 --> 00:19:32,511
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

538
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:35,481
Yu Jun's hairstyle is already ruined.

539
00:19:35,849 --> 00:19:37,183
He looked so adorable, though.

540
00:19:37,184 --> 00:19:38,250
- Right.
- Agreed.

541
00:19:38,585 --> 00:19:41,212
When he was getting washed
and showed his forehead,

542
00:19:41,236 --> 00:19:41,987
he looked so pretty.

543
00:19:41,988 --> 00:19:44,623
His forehead is really round.

544
00:19:44,624 --> 00:19:45,624
It's a perfect circle.

545
00:19:46,827 --> 00:19:48,861
(Big circle, little circle)

546
00:19:49,663 --> 00:19:51,631
(Are you filming me?)

547
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:54,934
(Up close)

548
00:19:57,237 --> 00:19:58,103
You look great.

549
00:19:58,872 --> 00:20:00,973
(Shall we, the two circles,
have some fun?)

550
00:20:01,141 --> 00:20:03,075
(Will you play with me?)

551
00:20:03,477 --> 00:20:04,710
- Bonk.
- Bonk.

552
00:20:05,645 --> 00:20:07,079
- Bonk.
- Bonk.

553
00:20:08,648 --> 00:20:11,750
(These cute circles are having fun
without any tears.)

554
00:20:12,152 --> 00:20:12,985
Snacks!

555
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,320
Snacks!

556
00:20:14,788 --> 00:20:15,722
You want some snacks?

557
00:20:16,877 --> 00:20:17,690
Snacks?

558
00:20:18,558 --> 00:20:19,324
Do you want one?

559
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:25,831
(Let me taste it too.)

560
00:20:26,032 --> 00:20:27,733
This doesn't really taste like anything,
but it's weirdly addictive.

561
00:20:27,734 --> 00:20:29,434
(I want more.)

562
00:20:29,703 --> 00:20:31,904
(Feet tapping in anticipation)

563
00:20:32,873 --> 00:20:35,641
(Snack express delivery
straight to Yu Jun's mouth)

564
00:20:37,577 --> 00:20:38,744
Open wide.

565
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:41,180
Open wide, and I'll give it to you.

566
00:20:43,016 --> 00:20:45,551
Yu Jun is really good
at using his tiny hands.

567
00:20:46,553 --> 00:20:47,353
Snacks.

568
00:20:48,021 --> 00:20:49,888
(Again?)

569
00:20:49,889 --> 00:20:50,656
Snacks.

570
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:54,059
You really love snacks.

571
00:20:54,060 --> 00:20:55,562
But you have to eat a real meal later.

572
00:20:56,496 --> 00:20:58,230
Snacks.

573
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:00,132
Pass me one more.

574
00:21:01,835 --> 00:21:03,640
Yu Jun, this is seriously the last one.
You have to eat dinner later.

575
00:21:03,703 --> 00:21:05,238
I'll break it in half
and give you a small piece.

576
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:11,944
(The snack airplane is taking off.)

577
00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:17,116
What's that heart on your cheek?

578
00:21:17,884 --> 00:21:18,817
I think he broke out.

579
00:21:19,705 --> 00:21:20,585
What is that? It's a pimple patch.

580
00:21:20,586 --> 00:21:21,586
You picked a cute one.

581
00:21:21,587 --> 00:21:22,921
You're so Gen-Z.

582
00:21:22,922 --> 00:21:24,489
Cute, right?
There are so many designs now.

583
00:21:24,991 --> 00:21:27,225
- Cats and rabbits.
- There used to be only plain ones.

584
00:21:27,226 --> 00:21:28,226
I guess they have way more variety now.

585
00:21:28,227 --> 00:21:30,228
(Sleepy but still wants snacks)

586
00:21:31,031 --> 00:21:32,098
Yu Jun must be sleepy.

587
00:21:32,532 --> 00:21:33,799
- I'm sleepy too.
- He keeps rubbing his eyes.

588
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,334
- Am I a baby too?
- I'm a baby too.

589
00:21:35,802 --> 00:21:37,937
I think we're the babies here.
We sleep way more than Yu Jun does.

590
00:21:38,605 --> 00:21:41,607
Yu Jun goes to bed at 9 or 10 p.m.

591
00:21:42,309 --> 00:21:44,644
But you guys sleep at 4 a.m.,
so of course you're tired.

592
00:21:44,645 --> 00:21:46,112
("You guys")

593
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:50,583
(Sleep is the best medicine.)

594
00:21:54,588 --> 00:21:56,589
(Oh my gosh!)

595
00:21:57,490 --> 00:21:59,491
(Bumping into a bump)

596
00:22:01,261 --> 00:22:04,930
(He is startled for a second,
but slowly falls back asleep.)

597
00:22:07,834 --> 00:22:09,034
(Startled)

598
00:22:09,469 --> 00:22:11,370
(Is he awake?)

599
00:22:11,371 --> 00:22:13,739
(No.)

600
00:22:15,275 --> 00:22:19,712
(Sleep tight,
big circle and little circle.)

601
00:22:21,614 --> 00:22:23,615
(Is he sleeping well?)

602
00:22:24,184 --> 00:22:25,751
(He's fast asleep.)

603
00:22:25,986 --> 00:22:27,367
(The guys in the back are out too.)

604
00:22:28,154 --> 00:22:30,789
(How adorable.)

605
00:22:36,863 --> 00:22:40,466
(Taking a picture
of the sleeping little circle)

606
00:22:41,835 --> 00:22:42,535
(Arriving at the spa)

607
00:22:42,536 --> 00:22:44,603
- Hello.
- Hi.

608
00:22:44,604 --> 00:22:47,239
We have five adults...

609
00:22:47,975 --> 00:22:49,308
and one baby.

610
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:51,143
I think he pooped.

611
00:22:51,144 --> 00:22:52,177
- Really?
- Yeah.

612
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:54,880
So that's why he was straining earlier.

613
00:22:56,016 --> 00:22:58,951
(Yu Jun woke up from his nap
the moment they arrived.)

614
00:22:59,452 --> 00:23:02,087
(Grunting)

615
00:23:04,023 --> 00:23:05,090
(Was that him straining just now?)

616
00:23:05,091 --> 00:23:07,125
(Fists clenched)

617
00:23:08,695 --> 00:23:11,263
(Grunting)

618
00:23:13,266 --> 00:23:17,269
(Yu Jun keeps groaning,
and the members have no idea why.)

619
00:23:18,672 --> 00:23:19,772
Hold on.

620
00:23:19,773 --> 00:23:22,308
(Changing a diaper with strong suspicion
for the first time.)

621
00:23:25,378 --> 00:23:26,778
Yu Jun is being so good.

622
00:23:26,779 --> 00:23:27,914
How can he be this calm?

623
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:29,348
Yu Jun, it's okay.

624
00:23:29,516 --> 00:23:31,150
- He's not even crying.
- It's all right.

625
00:23:32,085 --> 00:23:33,285
Let's change your diaper.

626
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:36,623
You're supposed to tear the sides open.

627
00:23:36,856 --> 00:23:38,323
Oh man, he really pooped.

628
00:23:38,324 --> 00:23:40,759
- He pooped.
- He pooped!

629
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:41,628
Take it off.

630
00:23:41,629 --> 00:23:43,562
This is my first time seeing baby poop.

631
00:23:43,563 --> 00:23:44,896
Good job.

632
00:23:44,897 --> 00:23:45,764
He pooped a lot.

633
00:23:45,765 --> 00:23:47,532
Way more than I expected.

634
00:23:49,502 --> 00:23:51,069
But it's surprisingly clean.

635
00:23:51,070 --> 00:23:52,704
Quick, fold it up and throw it away.

636
00:23:52,705 --> 00:23:54,372
(Wiping him down with wet wipes)

637
00:23:54,373 --> 00:23:56,341
Is there a restroom nearby?

638
00:23:56,342 --> 00:23:57,309
You should go wash up in the restroom.

639
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:59,144
There are shower stalls right here.

640
00:23:59,979 --> 00:24:01,548
- Let's go, Yu Jun.
- Aren't your legs falling asleep?

641
00:24:02,348 --> 00:24:03,181
Let's go.

642
00:24:03,616 --> 00:24:04,789
You did a great job pooping!

643
00:24:05,452 --> 00:24:06,285
So cute.

644
00:24:06,853 --> 00:24:08,854
Yu Jun, your little butt is so cute.

645
00:24:10,323 --> 00:24:12,057
His parents must be so happy.

646
00:24:12,258 --> 00:24:14,326
He's incredibly well-behaved.

647
00:24:15,261 --> 00:24:16,462
Is it clean now?

648
00:24:16,796 --> 00:24:17,662
Done.

649
00:24:18,364 --> 00:24:19,798
Sorry, Yu Jun.

650
00:24:19,799 --> 00:24:20,765
(Wiping his bottom with a clean towel)

651
00:24:20,766 --> 00:24:21,900
Use the towel.

652
00:24:21,901 --> 00:24:23,468
How are you this calm?

653
00:24:23,469 --> 00:24:24,769
(Crowded)

654
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:26,572
(Baby Yu Jun calmly accepting
everyone's touch)

655
00:24:26,573 --> 00:24:29,575
Let's go inside
and put a fresh diaper on him.

656
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:32,010
Like this.

657
00:24:32,011 --> 00:24:33,979
(YEONJUN even takes over diaper duty.)

658
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:35,381
We should dry him off a bit.

659
00:24:36,282 --> 00:24:38,416
(Drying service included)

660
00:24:38,417 --> 00:24:39,951
- Is it good now?
- All done.

661
00:24:40,687 --> 00:24:41,754
Good job, Yu Jun.

662
00:24:41,755 --> 00:24:42,755
(Diaper change complete)

663
00:24:43,056 --> 00:24:44,757
Even with all five of us,

664
00:24:44,758 --> 00:24:46,325
just changing a wet diaper was
a massive struggle before.

665
00:24:46,326 --> 00:24:48,293
(Time to enjoy the sauna,
feeling refreshed)

666
00:24:48,294 --> 00:24:50,896
We're on the third floor.
Let's get off here.

667
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:53,932
We're getting off.

668
00:24:53,933 --> 00:24:55,134
Ta-da!

669
00:24:55,401 --> 00:24:56,634
Yu Jun has officially entered the spa!

670
00:24:57,029 --> 00:24:58,667
Look, there's a toy cart for you, Yu Jun.

671
00:24:58,691 --> 00:24:59,263
Perfect.

672
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,840
(Hold my hand!)

673
00:25:01,841 --> 00:25:02,874
- Yu Jun wants you to hold his hand.
- He wants your hand.

674
00:25:02,875 --> 00:25:04,543
(The new Choi trio)

675
00:25:04,677 --> 00:25:05,477
Let's look around.

676
00:25:05,478 --> 00:25:06,711
(He can't give up
his favorite toy cart, even at the spa.)

677
00:25:06,712 --> 00:25:08,647
I want to go check out
the comic book cafe.

678
00:25:08,882 --> 00:25:09,682
(Hold my hand.)
Okay.

679
00:25:12,786 --> 00:25:14,386
Spas are so nice these days.

680
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:16,055
- It's huge.
- Seriously.

681
00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:17,890
What game is this?

682
00:25:18,424 --> 00:25:19,991
It's been forever since I played this.

683
00:25:20,326 --> 00:25:22,227
- "Puyo Puyo."
- This one is "SNOW BROS."

684
00:25:22,729 --> 00:25:23,595
There's so much to play.

685
00:25:23,596 --> 00:25:24,697
Is there anything Yu Jun can play?

686
00:25:24,698 --> 00:25:25,764
There are capsule machines too.

687
00:25:26,432 --> 00:25:28,066
- Something Yu Jun can do?
- Probably the claw machine.

688
00:25:29,302 --> 00:25:31,537
(From Yu Jun's eye level)

689
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:34,473
Bonk.

690
00:25:35,375 --> 00:25:36,141
Bonk.
Bonk.

691
00:25:37,076 --> 00:25:38,110
(From the members' knee level)

692
00:25:38,278 --> 00:25:39,078
Okay.

693
00:25:39,079 --> 00:25:40,879
(YEONJUN has already taken a seat.)

694
00:25:41,014 --> 00:25:42,214
Sorry, Yu Jun!

695
00:25:44,617 --> 00:25:46,151
I missed this feeling so much!

696
00:25:46,152 --> 00:25:47,819
(His fingers move faster out of guilt.)

697
00:25:47,820 --> 00:25:49,754
- That one is closer.
- Should I push it down?

698
00:25:50,356 --> 00:25:51,956
If you could push that side,
that'd be perfect.

699
00:25:51,957 --> 00:25:53,091
(BEOMGYU and HUENINGKAI
tackle the claw machine.)

700
00:25:54,794 --> 00:25:56,695
(You're actually pretty good at this.)

701
00:25:57,096 --> 00:25:58,430
Wait. Oh, it's going to drop it.

702
00:25:58,565 --> 00:25:59,265
(No, it's not.)
Oh boy.

703
00:26:01,334 --> 00:26:02,734
(The toy got hooked on the claw.)

704
00:26:02,735 --> 00:26:05,003
What is even happening right now?

705
00:26:05,778 --> 00:26:07,971
(Yu Jun excitedly pushes the cart
behind his excited uncles.)

706
00:26:08,102 --> 00:26:10,489
It must be nice to walk around
because it's spacious.

707
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:14,605
(When it comes to gaming, the dads
completely forget about their son.)

708
00:26:15,808 --> 00:26:18,877
(Yu Jun is literally right behind you.)

709
00:26:18,878 --> 00:26:20,945
(I am winning this.)

710
00:26:22,148 --> 00:26:25,016
(The definitive sigh of defeat)

711
00:26:25,651 --> 00:26:26,484
What?

712
00:26:27,219 --> 00:26:28,654
I lost one life,
and it's already game over?

713
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:31,856
(Their situation isn't looking
any better.)

714
00:26:31,857 --> 00:26:33,692
How can something this ridiculous happen?

715
00:26:34,099 --> 00:26:35,432
Isn't this ridiculous?

716
00:26:37,196 --> 00:26:39,531
Yu Jun, I was trying to win you a plushie.

717
00:26:39,532 --> 00:26:40,598
What happened?

718
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,133
The toy's string got tangled in the claw.

719
00:26:42,768 --> 00:26:43,701
Hold on.

720
00:26:44,436 --> 00:26:45,936
Let me roll up your pants.

721
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:49,207
(YEONJUN takes charge of styling Yu Jun.)

722
00:26:49,208 --> 00:26:50,742
I'll style you, Yu Jun.

723
00:26:52,511 --> 00:26:53,578
Let me fix your look.

724
00:26:53,579 --> 00:26:55,046
(An incredibly enthusiastic stylist)

725
00:26:57,349 --> 00:26:58,382
Like this.

726
00:26:58,383 --> 00:26:59,457
(Willingly letting YEONJUN style him)

727
00:26:59,458 --> 00:27:02,086
Let's tuck this side in slightly...

728
00:27:02,555 --> 00:27:04,556
to give it that effortless, casual vibe.

729
00:27:05,024 --> 00:27:05,757
Hold on.

730
00:27:06,392 --> 00:27:07,926
(Staggering)

731
00:27:09,094 --> 00:27:10,661
It looks so stylish!

732
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:12,897
Yu Jun, you've got swag.

733
00:27:13,265 --> 00:27:14,232
Don't you think so?

734
00:27:15,201 --> 00:27:16,135
Done.

735
00:27:16,834 --> 00:27:18,201
Look at you, Yu Jun.

736
00:27:18,467 --> 00:27:19,967
(The effortless-chic front tuck
and those adorable mozzarella legs)

737
00:27:19,967 --> 00:27:21,034
You look so cool, Yu Jun.

738
00:27:21,467 --> 00:27:22,801
(And those plump,
squishy cheeks to top it off)

739
00:27:23,001 --> 00:27:24,567
I think we've spent
about 20 dollars on this already.

740
00:27:24,567 --> 00:27:25,967
I'm not giving up until we win one.

741
00:27:27,201 --> 00:27:29,101
I thought we'd get it on the first try.

742
00:27:30,801 --> 00:27:33,101
Hey! I have an idea!

743
00:27:33,667 --> 00:27:35,201
- Should we just reach in?
- Let's just grab it.

744
00:27:35,201 --> 00:27:36,034
Okay.

745
00:27:36,034 --> 00:27:37,301
I'm hitting the button.

746
00:27:37,301 --> 00:27:39,434
(Never letting it go)

747
00:27:39,434 --> 00:27:40,334
Grab it by the ears!

748
00:27:40,901 --> 00:27:41,867
Don't let it go!

749
00:27:42,201 --> 00:27:45,001
(They finally succeed.)

750
00:27:45,367 --> 00:27:46,267
Let's give it to Yu Jun.

751
00:27:46,267 --> 00:27:47,434
Yu Jun!

752
00:27:47,434 --> 00:27:48,267
Did you see this?

753
00:27:48,267 --> 00:27:49,701
Yu Jun!

754
00:27:49,701 --> 00:27:51,734
We finally got one for you!
That was so hard.

755
00:27:52,267 --> 00:27:54,301
- Nice. You actually got it.
- Right?

756
00:27:54,601 --> 00:27:57,134
Yu Jun, this puppy cost us
about 50 dollars.

757
00:27:57,146 --> 00:27:58,289
How did you even manage that?

758
00:27:58,601 --> 00:28:00,867
- To be honest, we didn't really...
- Yu Jun.

759
00:28:01,834 --> 00:28:03,101
- You don't want it?
- We worked so hard.

760
00:28:03,101 --> 00:28:04,701
Yu Jun, isn't the puppy cute?

761
00:28:05,934 --> 00:28:09,334
Yu Jun, if you don't want it,
can I have it?

762
00:28:10,669 --> 00:28:13,049
(Yu Jun is off to find new entertainment.)

763
00:28:13,138 --> 00:28:14,905
Don't babies usually like
shiny, flashy things?

764
00:28:14,906 --> 00:28:15,773
Exactly.

765
00:28:15,875 --> 00:28:17,542
That side seems to have
a lot of flashy stuff.

766
00:28:18,017 --> 00:28:19,751
(Found it!)

767
00:28:21,420 --> 00:28:23,855
Yu Jun, you still love stairs the most
out of everything here.

768
00:28:24,924 --> 00:28:27,225
(Yu Jun, the legendary stair-loving baby)

769
00:28:27,226 --> 00:28:28,727
Swoosh!

770
00:28:29,095 --> 00:28:30,028
Swoosh!

771
00:28:30,029 --> 00:28:32,331
He ditched the cart immediately
and went straight for the stairs.

772
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:35,467
Okay. Turn around.

773
00:28:35,768 --> 00:28:37,035
- Turn around.
- Let's go up.

774
00:28:38,171 --> 00:28:40,506
- On 1, 2...
- Should we make him fly?

775
00:28:40,940 --> 00:28:41,940
On 1, 2!

776
00:28:42,441 --> 00:28:45,075
(A human airplane for going uphill)

777
00:28:45,076 --> 00:28:46,477
He just goes whichever way we steer him.

778
00:28:46,478 --> 00:28:47,745
On 1, 2, 3.

779
00:28:47,746 --> 00:28:48,880
(Taking off one more time!)

780
00:28:48,881 --> 00:28:50,348
(Happy)

781
00:28:53,145 --> 00:28:54,225
We can't go up too far.

782
00:28:54,627 --> 00:28:55,260
Going up again?

783
00:28:55,389 --> 00:28:57,389
We'll only go up a few and come back down.

784
00:28:58,458 --> 00:29:00,605
(They should've realized it then.)

785
00:29:00,860 --> 00:29:01,653
Stair time.

786
00:29:03,195 --> 00:29:05,604
(Yu Jun's intense love for the stairs)

787
00:29:05,637 --> 00:29:06,778
I can't believe this.

788
00:29:07,213 --> 00:29:08,487
Let's do "Bonk!" instead.

789
00:29:08,895 --> 00:29:10,469
I'll play "Bonk!" instead.

